 day that changed everything for her.  The Circle of Friends had been strong then.  Although recovering from a broken heart, Maritzia had been strong, too, sure of her faith, sure of the rightness of her path.  She fought back tears as she thought of the friends now scattered, some gone forever:  Shacaree and Renaldare, Salelili and Tinvarian, Gatsu and Sumida, even Balumbus and Laika, who though of evil nature, were still Friends.  But that was before the news that shattered her life and set her on the path that led her to this point.<br><br>A heavy sigh broke from her as she thought of that day and the dark days that followed.  She had been in her 18th season when she received the  urgent summons from her Master at the Temple.  It had surprised her, because he had never summoned her in such a way before, rather waiting for her to come to him as she needed.  She had been fighting in the Warrens, honing her skills, and Gatsu came frequently to watch over her.  He knew of her sadness over the marriage of Shacaree and Renaldare, and he had been extremely kind to her.  He was much too skilled a warrior to find much challenge there <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showNextMessage?topicID=338.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=338.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/classic/addReply.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"><a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.threadControl?topicID=338.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm10.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=338.